header.gameNote: FLINT HILLS RESOURCES ISLANDER CLASSIC AT CORPUS CHRISTI TX

article.headline: Yale 96, Savannah State 67
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Dominick Martin scored 18 points off the bench and Yale shot nearly 60 percent from the field in a 96-67 victory against Savannah State in the Islanders Classic consolation game Friday night. Martin was 9-of-13 from the field for Yale (6-6), which made 39 of 66 shots (59 percent). Sam Kaplan added 15 points on 6-of-7 shooting. Joseph Flegler scored 17 points to lead Savannah State (1-14), which had just two field goals and seven points in the first half of a 90-45 loss to tournament host Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Thursday. Kaplan scored eight of his points during a 17-1 run that put Yale ahead 64-39 with 14:05 left in the game.
